Two separate issues here:

## 1. `StaticResource` doesn't update at runtime

`StaticResource` resolves **once** at XAML load time. For runtime theme switching, use **`DynamicResource`**:

```xml
<!-- ❌ Won't update -->
<Label TextColor="{StaticResource PrimaryTextColor}" />

<!-- ✅ Will update -->
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource PrimaryTextColor}" />
```

Then swap dictionaries at runtime:

```csharp
var mergedDictionaries = Application.Current.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
mergedDictionaries.Clear();
mergedDictionaries.Add(isDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
```

## 2. Activity restart on system theme change

Android destroys and recreates the `Activity` on configuration changes like dark mode. In your `MainActivity.cs`, add `UiMode` to `ConfigChanges`:

```csharp
[Activity(
    Theme = "@style/Maui.SplashTheme",
    ConfigurationChanges = ConfigChanges.ScreenSize
        | ConfigChanges.Orientation
        | ConfigChanges.UiMode   // ← prevents restart on dark mode toggle
        | ConfigChanges.ScreenLayout
        | ConfigChanges.SmallestScreenSize)]
public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity { }
```

Then detect the system change and apply your theme:

```csharp
// In App.xaml.cs
Application.Current.RequestedThemeChanged += (s, e) =>
{
    bool isDark = e.RequestedTheme == AppTheme.Dark;
    var merged = Resources.MergedDictionaries;
    merged.Clear();
    merged.Add(isDark ? new DarkTheme() : new LightTheme());
};
```

**TL;DR** — `StaticResource` → `DynamicResource` for live updates; add `ConfigChanges.UiMode` to stop the Activity restart.
